title: PPPP’s Makhdoom Fakhar Zaman wins PS- 57 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) candidate Makhdoom Fakhar Zaman has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-57, Matiari-II, by securing 52,175 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Syed Jalal Shah of Grand Democratic Alliance, who bagged vote 44,873.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 52.80 %.
